Class Permutate

java.lang.Object
  DogPoundBreakout.Permutate

public class Permutate
extends java.lang.Object

COPYRIGHT (C) 2005 Rob Bauer. All Rights Reserved. Add permutation functions to the vector object.
Create a new Permutate object with a supplied string and it will automatically generate all the permutations available (assuming there's enough java heap space).
Permuation algorithm modelled after: http://www.codeguru.com/Cpp/Cpp/algorithms/combinations/article.php /c7605/ By srini_gct

Method Detail

permutateParts

private void permutateParts(char[] cprefix,
                            char[] csuffix)
Recursively find the unique string patterns and rotate each of them
for example: "123" is 1(23) which is a unique pattern of 123.
and 1(32) is a unique pattern of 132. These can be rotated:
123 rotates to: 231 and 312
132 rotates to: 321 and 213
Function recursively finds 123 and 132 and then rotates the unique patterns to produce the permutations
Permuation algorithm modelled after: http://www.codeguru.com/Cpp/Cpp/algorithms/combinations /article.php/c7605/#more

Parameters:
cprefix - character array containing the string prefix
csuffix - character array containing the string suffix
